Relax20092506076
116
Reviewed 4 weeks ago
via mobile
I've had better
We thought we would check this out after watching a couple of you tube videos. As indicated, it is at the end of an alley. Place was busy. We tried the Banh Xeo as well as the pork skewers. We had already had Banh Xeo twice since we've been Vietnam. Once in Ho Chi Minh and once at the Son Tra Market. I have to say this would be by least favorite so far. The pork skewers were great! The Banh Xeo not so much. I found it to thick and oily, not like the other two we had. Everyone there however looked like they were enjoying it. It was edible, and the fresh herbs, sprouts and cucumbers were tasty when rolled up together. However, what I didn't like was their "sauce". It was clearly a thick gravy, the kind you have when you make meatballs and gravy. It didn't appeal to me at all, especially on fresh vegetables and lettuce. I was so looking forward to a light tasty dipping sauce. However, like I said, those there liked it. Just be prepared their "dipping sauce" is a gravy. If you don't mind it, then you will enjoy it.
Show less
